A certificate that I find to be very meaningful – a first aid certificate.
This is one of the skill certificates that I consider to be important, besides my driver’s license!
Let me make it clearer: First aid measures are actually emergency responses taken in the event of sudden incidents, that is, the rescue efforts carried out before the ambulance arrives.
As is well known, there is actually a certain amount of time that passes before the ambulance arrives after an accident occurs, and it is precisely this period that is the most critical.
This is the moment when emergency medical attention is needed.
If I actually suffer a heart attack, a stroke, or a sudden stop in breathing, then the window of opportunity for saving our lives is only four minutes—those precious “golden four minutes”!
It’s so important that the people around us know how to perform first aid!
When someone around us collapses, we can use our professional knowledge to help them. Instead of just standing there motionless and doing nothing, that feeling of helplessness is truly terrifying.
“In China, according to official data, three million people die accidentally each year. The most dangerous cause of death is sudden cardiac arrest.”
Across the United States, on average, 15% of people can be saved.
At the casino hotels in Las Vegas, 70 to 80 percent of people can be rescued; in Shanghai and Beijing, the rate is less than 1 percent.”
This is what Lu Le, the founder of First Reaction, said.
If a person experiences cardiac arrest, with no breathing or heartbeat, pressing the philtrum (the spot between the nose and the upper lip) will be of no use.
Artificial respiration and chest compressions must be performed in order to have a chance of saving the person.
I’ve noticed that not many of us currently have the awareness to learn first aid skills. However, by the time something happens, it might already be too late. Therefore, I would like to urge everyone to learn these skills so that we can respond promptly in case of emergencies.
Who knows, it might even save a person’s life!
You can sign up for a first aid certification at the local Red Cross training center. I registered at the Red Cross training center in Zhuhai, and there are even discounts available for students.
PS: The last picture shows the goals I set for myself to achieve before I turned 25. Adding a first-aid certificate to that list was also something I did a few months ago, and I’ve actually managed to accomplish it!
Next, I need to take exams for other certificates I want to obtain. I plan to get a scuba diving certificate. I saw on REDnote that there’s also a certification for first aid in diving, and it seems that you need to have a first aid certificate to be eligible to take the scuba diving exam. So, in fact, a first aid certificate is really useful!
