Ingredients for the beauty and skin-nourishing soup:
The benefits of White Fungus (Tremella fuciformis): It has a sweet taste and a neutral nature, and it affects the lung, stomach, and kidney meridians. It is effective in strengthening the essence, nourishing the kidneys, moistening the intestines, benefiting the stomach, replenishing qi, harmonizing the blood, strengthening the heart, nourishing yin, moistening the lungs, promoting the production of body fluids, enhancing physical vitality, benefiting the brain, invigorating the mind, beautifying the skin, and prolonging life. It is used to treat conditions such as cough due to
The effects of peach gum: It has a bitter taste and a neutral nature, and it belongs to the Large Intestine and Bladder meridians.
Benefits: It promotes blood circulation, helps with urinary disorders, stops diarrhea, relieves pain, and also provides hydration while soothing the intestines. For those suffering from constipation, consuming more peach gum can be beneficial.
The effects of goji berries: They have a neutral nature and a sweet taste, and they are associated with the liver and stomach meridians.
Benefits the liver and improves eyesight, nourishes the liver and kidneys, enhances skin fairness and beauty, replenishes body fluids, and slows down the aging process.
The benefits of red dates: They have a sweet taste and a mild nature, and they affect the spleen and stomach meridians. Red dates help to strengthen the spleen and stomach, replenish qi, generate body fluids, nourish the blood, and calm the mind. Those with weak spleen and stomach function, insufficient qi and blood, or insomnia can benefit from consuming more red dates.
The benefits of longan pulp: It has a sweet taste and a warm nature, and it affects the heart and spleen meridians. It is suitable for those with deficiencies in both the heart and spleen.
Longan pulp can also moisturize the skin and enhance its beauty, nourish the blood and soothe the mind, benefit the heart and spleen, strengthen yang and boost energy. It is suitable for people with anemia as well as those who suffer from insomnia.
The effects of lotus seeds: They have a sweet and astringent taste, a neutral nature, and are associated with the heart, spleen, and kidney meridians.
It helps to soothe the mind and calm the nerves, alleviate symptoms such as palpitations and insomnia, address stomach weakness and forgetfulness, relieve irritability and thirst, provide nourishment to replenish deficiencies in the body, and stop excessive urination and sperm leakage.
