Actually, there are many considerations when it comes to the clothing choices for girls who are slightly overweight.
Girls who are overweight should not wear skirts that are too short or too long; the length should be around the knees, just enough to cover the areas where their thighs are thicker.
If a skirt is too short, it will highlight the fat on the legs.
If it’s too long, it can give the impression of someone being short and overweight.
If you wear clothes that are divided into three sections – upper, middle, and lower – it can make you look taller naturally. Just use different colors for the upper body, skirt, and stockings, and it will create an effect that makes you appear more slender.
In fact, many dark-colored clothes are a staple for girls who are slightly overweight (the author can attest to this firsthand). Dark colors are also an excellent way to conceal a fuller figure, and elegant black skirts are a favorite choice for such girls.
Wearing dark-colored clothes, especially a black skirt, can make you appear slimmer.
If your calves are quite thick, try not to wear socks and shoes that draw too much attention to them.
The more popular it is, the better. Also, the colors shouldn’t be too bright.
To prevent people from noticing your legs and feet and thus giving the impression that you are overweight.
For slightly overweight girls, it’s really important to teach them the tricks of how to dress well and match their clothes properly.
Chubby girls should definitely avoid wearing tight skirts. Also, the tops should not be too short or tucked into the skirt, as this can make people feel uncomfortable. If you have thick legs, wear black stockings or mesh stockings (the ones with a fine pattern). Choose a soft, printed flared skirt and pair it with a top with a V-neck; this can effectively cover up any potential shortcomings.
Of course, even slightly plump girls have their own considerations when it comes to wearing short skirts.
A chubby girl wearing a short skirt should choose a top that matches the color of the skirt; this will give the appearance of a taller figure due to the added height.
A short skirt paired with high heels can make your legs look longer and slimmer—this is definitely the most trendy combination for summer!
If you’re a girl with a larger upper body but thinner legs, I recommend choosing a stylish one-piece skirt that adds a glamorous look.
It not only covers your big belly, but also highlights your best features.
A-line skirts can really make you look slimmer and are more suitable for girls who are a bit curvy. For the top, choose something a bit tighter to create a layered look, which will also help you appear more slender.
A simple white T-shirt paired with a short skirt – even plump girls can give it a try.
Even slightly plump girls can look stylish when they dress properly.
As long as one can master the rules of clothing combination, even slightly plump girls can become the center of attention.
Now that I’ve made changes to my clothing style, I also need to exercise more in my daily life and strive to get rid of the label of being a “slightly overweight girl” as soon as possible 😄
The 18th “World Beverage Innovation Awards” are an award presented jointly by FoodBev Media and the German international beer, brewing, and beverage industry exhibition, Brau Beviale, which takes place in Nuremberg.
A total of 279 entries were received from 25 countries, representing 22 different categories.
On October 15th, the list of finalists for the competition was announced. The final list of winners will be published online on November 11th (British Summer Time).
We see that the LP28 sugar-free yogurt from Yuanqi Forest has been nominated for the Best Dairy Beverage Award, Yili Amuji’s “GOGO Wuhan” marketing campaign has been nominated for the Best Marketing Campaign Award, and the packaging collaboration between PepsiCo and People’s Daily’s new media has also been nominated for the Best Packaging Design/Label Award.
Laura Nettle, Senior Marketing Director at FoodBev Media, stated: “We are delighted to celebrate the 18th anniversary of the annual World Beverage Innovation Awards together with Brau Beviale.”
From new flavors, concepts, and features to branding, packaging, and manufacturing processes, we observe trends in the beverage industry as the sector continues to innovate in more sustainable ways.
The World Beverage Innovation Awards recognize the most ambitious new products and developments from both established and emerging brands in the global beverage industry this year.
Here is the complete list of finalists for each category in the finals:
The technology developed by the Ardagh Group enables 100% of recycled glass to be remelted into new bottles.
The water is packaged in bag-in-box containers, with boxes that are 100% recyclable. This reduces packaging waste by 66% and carbon emissions by 97%.
LatCub is 100% biodegradable, uses less paper, and does not contain any glues or tapes that are harmful to the environment.
The technology developed by the Ardagh Group enables 100% of recycled glass to be remelted and used to create new bottles.
The final list of winners will be announced on November 11th (British Summer Time) on the FoodBev Media YouTube channel. FBIF will continue to keep you updated, so stay tuned!
