A few days ago, abroad, millions of Porsche 911s and tens of millions of supercars from the Chiron series were destroyed in just a few minutes!
Looking at the results, it makes sense that the price is higher!
Let the spirit of the university resonate in harmony with the spirit of the times – Xinhua News Agency
The so-called "university spirit" refers to a series of educational philosophies and value pursuits that have been gradually established over the long term in the development of a university, representing the very essence of the institution.
From ancient times to the present, the spirit of universities has been of paramount importance for the development of politics, economics, culture, technology, society, and even the progress of a nation as a whole.
Since the birth of the world’s first modern university, universities have undertaken a unique mission that sets them apart from other social organizations. For the universities in our country, which emerged during times of national crisis, their spirit has been deeply influenced by traditional culture and the changes of the times. They advocate for the values of “cultivating virtue to benefit society” and “improving oneself, regulating one’s family, governing the state, and bringing peace to the world,” as well as the patriotic commitment to “strengthening the nation through education.”
Currently, the trends of informatization and internationalization in higher education are becoming increasingly evident. The competition in education, technology, and talent on a global scale is intensifying. As an important "supply-side" component of higher education, its structural reforms are facing unprecedented opportunities and challenges.
In particular, the introduction of the "Comprehensive Plan for the Development of World-Class Universities and Disciplines" demonstrates our country's confidence and determination in transitioning from a major player in higher education to a powerhouse in this field. It also sets higher and more modern requirements for the development of universities.
How can we strive to become among the world’s best in a relatively short period of time, and on the basis of existing gaps, accelerate the establishment of several world-class universities and a number of world-class disciplines, thereby achieving a “leapfrogging” effect?
In addition to having firm confidence in their goals, the path they choose, and their own capabilities, universities should also fully leverage three key advantages: 1. The advantage of being latecomers: By continuously attracting outstanding academic talents from abroad and learning from the advanced experiences of world-class universities, they can significantly improve their academic standards and the quality of education provided. 2. The cultural advantage: By inheriting the wisdom accumulated over five thousand years of Chinese civilization and promoting the development of excellent traditional culture, universities can unite people, build a strong brand, and enhance their reputation. 3. The institutional advantage: As socialist countries,
It is particularly important to recognize that building world-class universities cannot mean that all universities should look the same. While each university should leverage its strengths, it must also showcase its unique personality and characteristics.
The distinctive features of a school should not only reflect the common Chinese characteristics but also embody each school's unique goals, educational traditions, and resource endowments.
In the case of Zhejiang University, we focus on highlighting three distinctive aspects in our educational approach: First, we emphasize the cultivation of innovative and entrepreneurial talents by creating an integrated educational environment that combines science and education, as well as collaboration between universities and enterprises, thereby forming a comprehensive entrepreneurial education ecosystem. Second, we highlight the importance of interdisciplinary integration, promoting the optimization and adjustment of academic disciplines, fostering an institutional environment conducive to cross-disciplinary research, and actively nurturing emerging interdisciplinary fields and significant interdisciplinary achievements. Third, we stress the role of the university in serving society by engaging in extensive international exchanges and cooperation, with the
In this process, it is particularly important to always uphold the university spirit and ensure that it resonates in harmony with the spirit of the times.
For Zhejiang University, the motto “Seeking Truth and Innovation,” the shared values of “Diligent Learning, Cultivating Virtue, Making Clear Judgments, and Being Earnest,” as well as the mission statement “Embracing All Rivers and Streams, Promoting Truth and Virtue, Leading the People Forward, and Building Our Nation,” collectively constitute the latest expression of the university’s spirit.
This is an important guarantee for the school to maintain the correct direction in its educational efforts, continuously build up a high level of cultural heritage, and unite spiritual strength. It is rich in content and holds profound significance.
Among these, “Haina Jianghe” (Embracing Rivers and Streams) emphasizes the spirit of openness and inclusiveness, reflecting the ambition to harness the talents of the world for its own benefit, as demonstrated by adopting the high-quality educational philosophies of renowned international institutions. “Qizhen Houde” (Promoting Truth and Virtue) highlights the pursuit of truth and goodness, suggesting that universities should not only seek knowledge but also cultivate virtue and strengthen character. “Kaiwu Qianmin” (Advancing Society and Benefiting the People) embodies the spirit of innovation and reform, encompassing both the pursuit of
This series of spiritual concepts and value pursuits is precisely the essence of Zhejiang University’s 120 years of educational endeavors.
“The wise hear what is silent; the discerning perceive what has not yet taken form.”
Chinese universities should further focus on the overall situation of the cause of socialism with Chinese characteristics, deeply understand the historical context and mission of higher education, and accelerate their development into world-class institutions.
At the same time, it is essential to uphold humanistic care and independence, allowing the spirit of academia to interact with the spirit of the times and the national ethos. This interaction will foster a continuous drive for the prosperity of the nation and the rejuvenation of the race, as well as the realization of humanity's common ideals.
