Iranian President: If sanctions against Iran are lifted, there is a possibility of reaching an agreement in the nuclear negotiations – Xinhua News Agency
Xinhua News Agency, Tehran, December 11 (Reporters Gao Wencheng, Wang Shoubao) Iranian President Ebrahim Raisi said on December 11 in Tehran, the capital of Iran, that if the United States lifts its sanctions against Iran, negotiations on a comprehensive agreement regarding the Iranian nuclear issue could lead to a “good agreement.”
According to a message released on the website of the Iranian President, Raisi stated during a meeting with Iranian diplomats stationed in neighboring countries that by submitting proposals to the other parties involved in the Iran nuclear deal, Iran has demonstrated its sincerity in the negotiations.
If the United States makes up its mind, “the path to reaching an agreement will be clear.”
The parties involved in the Iran nuclear agreement began talks in April this year in Vienna, the capital of Austria, to discuss the resumption of compliance by both the United States and Iran.
A new round of talks began in Vienna on November 29, were temporarily suspended on December 3, and resumed on December 9.
