Xi Jinping sent a congratulatory letter to the 2021 Greater Bay Area Science Forum – Xinhua News Agency
Xinhua News Agency, Beijing, December 11th – On December 11th, President Xi Jinping sent a congratulatory letter to the 2021 Greater Bay Area Science Forum.
Xi Jinping pointed out that the world today is undergoing major changes unseen in a century, with global technological innovation entering a period of intense activity. A new round of scientific and technological revolution and industrial transformation has had a profound impact on the global economic structure.
The Guangdong-Hong Kong-Macao Greater Bay Area should focus on its strategic goal of becoming an international center for scientific and technological innovation, strive to build a global hub for innovation, and promote the development of emerging industries.
China is willing to work together with scientists from all over the world and international scientific and technological organizations to enhance international exchanges and cooperation in science and technology. We aim to strengthen research on major scientific issues, promote the resolution of common scientific and technological challenges, deepen collaboration on key scientific projects, and jointly advance the development of global science. This will bring greater benefits to humanity.
The 2021 Greater Bay Area Science Forum opened on that day in Guangzhou, Guangdong Province, with the theme “Exploring the Future, Sharing Science.” It was organized by the People’s Government of Guangdong Province.
