Education News: Beijing reduces the proportion of students with special talents entering junior high schools in 2016 – Xinhua News Agency
On the 21st and 22nd, the assessment for students with special talents entering junior high schools in Beijing was organized and implemented uniformly by the education commissions of each district.
This year, all districts in Beijing have reduced the proportion of students admitted based on their special talents, making the competition for these spots even more intense.
Taking Dongcheng District as an example, this year the proportion of students with special talents entering junior high schools from primary schools in this district does not exceed 5% of the total number of enrollment places in the entire district. The planned number of enrollments is 380 students, and the proportion of students who actually attend school does not exceed 10% of the school’s enrollment plan.
Any student who has outstanding skills in sports, arts, or technology and has registered online is eligible to participate in the special talent recruitment assessment.
To facilitate students in taking the examinations nearby, Dongcheng District has continued with the examination arrangement from last year, setting up 1 to 2 examination locations in each school district, for a total of 13 examination locations.
The examination centers are allocated according to the respective examination regions, and the testing periods are divided into hourly intervals. On the day of the exam, students will enter the designated examination centers at the appropriate times to take their tests within the corresponding examination regions.
On May 23rd, the District Education Admissions and Examinations Center published the list of students who passed the assessment online. Students can check their assessment results on the website.
