President of the Olympic Committee of Bosnia and Herzegovina: Firmly believe that China has the capability to organize a successful Winter Olympics during this special period – Xinhua News Agency
Xinhua News Agency, Sarajevo, December 11th: The president of the Bosnian Olympic Committee, Kvesić, recently stated that Bosnia is very much looking forward to the Beijing Winter Olympics and firmly believes that China has the capability to organize a successful Winter Olympic event during this special period.
Recently, Ji Ping, the Chinese Ambassador to Bosnia and Herzegovina, met with Kvetic, the President of the Olympic Committee of Bosnia and Herzegovina, at the Sarajevo Olympic Center.
During the meeting, Kvesić spoke positively about the relations between Bosnia and China. He mentioned that he had visited China during the 2008 Beijing Summer Olympics and was deeply impressed by the excellent organizational work displayed by the Chinese side. He expressed his confidence in China’s ability to host a successful Winter Olympics during a challenging period. Bosnia is looking forward to the Beijing Winter Olympics, and the Bosnian Olympic Committee is actively preparing for participation. Kvesić also expressed the hope that this event could serve as an opportunity to enhance sports exchanges and cooperation between Bosnia and China.
Ji Ping stated that China and Poland have a special “Olympic bond.”
The 1984 Winter Olympics in Sarajevo were successfully held here, and in just two months, the 2022 Winter Olympics in Beijing will also kick off, presenting the world with a simple, safe, and spectacular event.
We look forward to further enhancing exchanges and cooperation between the two countries in areas such as the preparation for winter sports events and the training of athletes. The Chinese Embassy in Bosnia and Herzegovina is willing to continue playing a bridging role. Taking the Beijing Winter Olympics as an opportunity, we aim to promote the deepening of cultural exchanges between the two nations, enabling their peoples to “move forward together towards the future.” We also wish the Bosnian athletes great success in Beijing.
Before the meeting, the Olympic Committee of Bosnia and Herzegovina held the award ceremony for the “10th Annual Best Athlete.” Ji Ping, as a special guest, presented awards to the best young athletes in Bosnia and Herzegovina.
Promotional videos for the Beijing Winter Olympics were played in a loop at the event site.
