“The Zhuihui Xiaoxiang 2021 China International Rail Transit and Equipment Manufacturing Industry Talent Summit has opened” – Rolling News – Hunan Daily Online – Huasheng Online
Hunan Daily, December 10th (All-media reporter Zhou Zhiheng) On the 9th, the “Intelligent Talent Gathering in Xiaoxiang” 2021 China International Rail Transit and Equipment Manufacturing Industry Talent Summit opened in Zhuzhou.
Wang Cheng, a member of the Standing Committee of the Provincial Party Committee and the head of the Provincial Party Committee Organization Department, attended the launching ceremony and delivered a speech.
Wang Cheng pointed out that hosting a talent summit is an important measure to implement the spirit of the Central Talent Work Conference and the 12th Provincial Party Congress, demonstrating Hunan’s sincere commitment to valuing, seeking, and making effective use of talent.
Hunan has an excellent tradition of recognizing, valuing, and respecting talent; it also provides a vast platform for supporting the development of talents and the environmental conditions necessary for achieving a better quality of life. In recent years, the province has vigorously implemented a talent-led development strategy. Guided by the Furong Talent Action Plan, it has established a comprehensive framework for attracting, nurturing, retaining, and utilizing talents. As a result, Hunan has become a fertile ground for talent growth and achievement, a hotbed for innovation and entrepreneurship, and a pleasant place to live and work.
Currently, Hunan is fully implementing the strategic positioning and mission of “Three Highs and Four New Initiatives.” It will further broaden its efforts to attract talented individuals, introduce more favorable policies to support innovation and entrepreneurship, concentrate additional resources, and create better conditions. Hunan looks forward to outstanding talents from all sectors contributing their wisdom and efforts to the province’s high-quality development.
The event site featured exhibition halls for Changsha, Zhuzhou, Xiangtan, as well as the Hunan Free Trade Pilot Zone. The Provincial Department of Science and Technology, the Provincial Department of Industry and Information Technology, and the Provincial Department of Human Resources and Social Security released key lists of technological innovation needs in the advanced manufacturing sector, a directory of talent requirements for the intelligent manufacturing industry, and a directory of talent needs for young professionals in the intelligent manufacturing industry at postdoctoral research stations.
Forty-eight large enterprises, including CRRC (China Railway Corporation), Zoomlion, and Yuanda Technology, recruited talents on-site. Nearly a thousand recent graduates from relevant fields and professionals from the community participated in the talent matchmaking programs.
